reviewText: Great movie. And a terrific movie to dissect and analyze when looking at Domestic Violence and learning about coordinated community responses.
Why is this movie worth so much. It really is not worth that. It is a good movie but you can watch it on lifetime they show it quite often. That is a stupid price.

Great DVD focuses on Abusive Relationship between teenagers and how often it is not taken seriously by others who are aware of the abuse concerning loved ones. This is an excellent movie to watch with your preteens and teens (both informative and educational).
This movie is good to show what can happen when you try to break up with a jealous boyfriend. when you see a friend getting abused you need to tell someone so this doesn't happen to your friend.

Good movie, but so true to life today.  Young women let this happen all of the time and no one interferes in their lives and tries to stop it.  Those who know or suspect whats going on in there loved one lives, should do something about it before it's too late.

A lesson learned is a life saved.

I haven't watched the 2nd movie that came with this one so I cannot make any comments about -- negative or otherwise.
A freaky storyline but a good movie. Any1 who likes Candace Cameron will enjoy it.
Incredible compeling story of an abusive relationship and the people who did not speak up but knew.
